h3. Issue Summary

When a user tries to open a Story directly from the board when using swimlanes by Stories and filtering the issues by an assignee, nothing happens.

h3. Environment

* Board;
* Using swimlanes by Story;
* Filtering the board by an assignee;

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a board;
 # Create a Story and a Sub-task under this story and assign the sub-task to a user (but not the story);
 # Filter the board clicking on the assignee you assigned the sub-task;
 # Click on the Story issue key in the Swimlane header. 

h3. Expected Results

The story should open.

h3. Actual Results

Nothing happens.

h3. Notes

The steps reproducing this behavior can be found [in this short video|https://cl.ly/3f9352759f09]

h3. Workaround

To open the Story, the user needs to open the sub-task and then access the Story from there.
